Democratic socialism is a political ideology advocating a democratic political system alongside a socialist economic system, involving a combination of political democracy with social ownership of the means of production. Federal highways receive federal money but state DOTs oversee the expenditure of capital. Medicaid is also state level. So to call all the services a form of Democratic Socialism is a bunch of malarky. If I could opt of of Social Security I would. If I could opt out of Medicare I would. I don't use USPS I use UPS or Fedex. Problem with supporters of Deoncratic Socialism here in this country is they don't even know what that term means. They dont know what Capitalism means either.
